ZXL Optimization Log - 2026-04-21
===================================

Session goal: Break through zstd-19 barrier toward LZMA/xz-9 territory.

Baseline (end of 2026-04-20 session):
  ntdll.dll:    0.4244 (beats bzip2-9, essentially ties zstd-19)
  kernel32.dll: 0.4304 (beats bzip2-9, ties zstd-19)
  user32.dll:   0.3521 (beats bzip2-9 & zstd-19)

Comparison targets (remaining):
  zstd-19:  ntdll ~0.428, kernel32 ~0.425, user32 ~0.349
  lzma/xz:  ntdll ~0.380, kernel32 ~0.375, user32 ~0.310
  7z Ultra: ntdll ~0.350, kernel32 ~0.345, user32 ~0.285

Planned phases for this session:
  1. CHAIN_DEPTH 2048 -> 4096 (marginal gain check)
  2. B4: 2-level hash (secondary 8-byte table for long-match candidates)
  3. B1: Binary tree hash chains (largest expected gain, most complex)
  4. B5: Content-adaptive block boundaries (PE section detection)

--- CHAIN_DEPTH 2048 -> 4096 ---
Tiny monotonic gain at ~2x compress cost. Accepted since diminishing returns
warn that deeper would not be productive.
  ntdll.dll:    0.4244 -> 0.4242  (-0.02 pts)
  kernel32.dll: 0.4304 -> 0.4303  (-0.01 pts)
  user32.dll:   0.3521 -> 0.3519  (-0.02 pts)

--- Block size 1 MB -> 4 MB (committed 57167b4) ---
ntdll goes from 3 blocks to 1 block: per-block rANS header overhead
(~11 KB for 21 freq tables) amortized over 4x more bytes. kernel32/user32
already fit in 1 block at 1 MB, so single-block files see no change from
larger blocks — only ntdll benefits on the block-count axis, but user32
got a modest parser-history win anyway (no block resets inside parse).
Tried 2 MB intermediate: ntdll -0.04, user32 -0.21. 4 MB better on ntdll.
  ntdll.dll:    0.4242 -> 0.4226  (-0.16 pts)
  kernel32.dll: 0.4303 -> 0.4303  (unchanged)
  user32.dll:   0.3519 -> 0.3498  (-0.21 pts)

--- N_LIT_CTX 16 -> 32 at 4 MB blocks (TRIED, REVERTED) ---
Hoped 4 MB blocks would amortize the 16 extra freq tables. But kernel32
is 836 KB (sub-block), so its overhead fraction didn't improve.
  ntdll.dll:    0.4226 -> 0.4234  (+0.08 pts)
  kernel32.dll: 0.4303 -> 0.4374  (+0.71 pts)
  user32.dll:   0.3498 -> 0.3525  (+0.27 pts)
Reverted.

--- B4: 2-level hash (committed 71ec9ce) ---
Secondary 8-byte hash chain (long_ht + long_next in MatchCtx). Walked
first in match_find so best_savings seeds with a high-quality long-match
candidate before the 4-byte chain saturates. match_update signature
extended with src_len to guard OOB read of 8 bytes at block tail.
Smaller than expected gain: CHAIN_DEPTH=4096 on the 4-byte chain was
already finding most of the long matches available.
  ntdll.dll:    0.4226 -> 0.4225  (-0.01 pts)
  kernel32.dll: 0.4303 -> 0.4303  (unchanged)
  user32.dll:   0.3498 -> 0.3497  (-0.01 pts)

--- Session summary ---
End of 2026-04-21: ntdll 0.4225, kernel32 0.4303, user32 0.3497.
Session delta vs start: -0.17 / 0 / -0.22 pts.
Still beats bzip2-9 on all files; still ~2 pts above zstd-19 on ntdll.
Next target: B1 binary-tree hash chains, or D1 compressed freq tables
(which would unlock N_LIT_CTX=32 without the overhead regression).

